    Demo Party 02 - Organization Respondent on case 03 (In Progress General Inquiry)
    ====================================================================

    Synthetic seed record for the case-management POC scoped application.
    This file is the SECOND of the 8-party demo dataset; it pairs with
    sibling party 01 (Person/Requester on the same case 03) to demonstrate
    that the polymorphic UI Policy works correctly on General Inquiry
    case types - one Person row + one Organization row on the same case
    exercises BOTH conditional branches simultaneously. Together with
    parties 03 through 08, this record satisfies AAP Section 0.4.1's
    seed-data folder requirements for `seed-data/parties/`.

    The complete 8-party fixture matrix:

        Party 01 - Person      / Requester  / parent case 03 (In Progress GI)
        Party 02 - Organization/ Respondent / parent case 03 (In Progress GI)  ## THIS FILE
        Party 03 - Person      / Witness    / parent case 04 (Pending GI)
        Party 04 - Person      / Requester  / parent case 05 (Resolved GI)
        Party 05 - Organization/ Respondent / parent case 05 (Resolved GI)
        Party 06 - Person      / Requester  / parent case 08 (In Progress Complaint)
        Party 07 - Organization/ Respondent / parent case 08 (In Progress Complaint)
        Party 08 - Person      / Witness    / parent case 09 (Resolved Complaint)

    The 8-party dataset thus exercises:
      * All 2 `party_type` choice values (Person x5, Organization x3) -
        this party contributes the FIRST of the three Organization
        entries; the Organization branch demonstrates that the
        conditional UI Policy at
        ../../ui_policy/x_[scope]_case_party_conditional_fields.xml
        correctly shows the <organization> reference field and HIDES
        the <person> reference field when party_type=Organization. As
        the FIRST Organization-branch row in the load sequence, this
        party is the canonical first invocation of the Organization
        branch when a fresh PDI imports the Update Set; subsequent
        Organization rows (parties 05 and 07) reuse the same branch
        with different parent cases and distinct or shared core_company
        references.
      * All 3 example `role_label` values (Requester x3, Respondent x3,
        Witness x2) - this party contributes the FIRST of the three
        Respondent entries (the others are party 05 on case 05 and
        party 07 on case 08). The Respondent role semantically
        represents the entity being investigated or that responds to
        the inquiry - the entity whose conduct, product, or position
        is the subject of the case.
      * 5 unique parent cases (03, 04, 05, 08, 09) - this party is
        the SECOND party on case 03 (paired with party 01's Person/
        Requester); cases 03, 05, and 08 each have TWO parties
        (Person + Organization) demonstrating the dual-party pattern.
        Case 03 is the canonical In Progress General Inquiry exemplar;
        case 08 plays the analogous role for the Complaint flow.
